                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>According to Pickersgill, pp. 551–552, Hull called on Mackenzie King at the
                    Citadel shortly after 4 o’clock and the two went for a drive, during which they
                    discussed the question of recognition of the French Committee of National
                    Liberation. No official record of the discussion has been found.</p>
            </div>
